Therefore, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.IT (Information Theory) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses logical depth, which is a topic in mathematical logic, and provides results on sets in P and EXP, which are related to algorithms and data structures, respectively. Therefore, cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) are also likely sub-categories.
